<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Medium to large sized species (5.6-8.7 mm). Antenna stout, antennomeres VII-X shortest (1.5-2.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide), III-VI similar or slender. Body convex. Elytra relatively broad, 1.4-1.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide. Aedeagus apically tapering and symmetric (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta alishanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545546" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meifena Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545550" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">20C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meihuai sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F gonocoxae G spermatheca H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545552" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22C</figureCitation>
) except 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. meihuai" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="meihuai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. meihuai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meifena Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545550" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">20C</figureCitation>
), ostium obliquely longitudinal and lacking cover; endophallic sclerites composed of primary sclerite with several teeth at apex in 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. igai" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="igai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. igai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta igai Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545549" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">19C</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. meifena" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="meifena">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. meifena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meifena Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545550" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">20C</figureCitation>
), with one secondary sclerite in 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. meihuai" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="meihuai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. meihuai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meihuai sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F gonocoxae G spermatheca H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545552" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22C, D</figureCitation>
) or two secondary sclerites in 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. alishanensis" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="alishanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. alishanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta alishanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545546" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16C, D</figureCitation>
) Ventrite VIII in females apically sclerotized, apical margin widely rounded and with dense short setae; spiculum long (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta alishanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545546" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta igai Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545549" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">19E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meifena Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545550" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">20E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meihuai sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F gonocoxae G spermatheca H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545552" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22E</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxae apically sclerotized and longitudinal, with dense, long setae along lateral and apical margins (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta alishanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545546" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta igai Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545549" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">19I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meifena Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545550" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">20I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meihuai sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F gonocoxae G spermatheca H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545552" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22F</figureCitation>
). Apical margin of abdominal ventrite V with one pair of rounded ridges at middle and slightly concave between ridges in males (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta alishanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545546" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta igai Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545549" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">19H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meifena Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545550" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">20H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meihuai sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F gonocoxae G spermatheca H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545552" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22I</figureCitation>
); widely rounded in females (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta alishanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545546" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meifena Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545550" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">20G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meihuai sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F gonocoxae G spermatheca H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545552" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22H</figureCitation>
) except concave in those of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. igai" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="igai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. igai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta igai Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545549" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">19G</figureCitation>
). Mesotibia lacking apical spine in males and tarsomere I not modified.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Larvae and adults feed on leaves of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Acer" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Acer" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Acer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Acer" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Sapindaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
